13.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,1304,1547]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1340,1367]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Distribution.</emphasis>
Thus far only recorded in Europe from 
<collectingCountry box="[796,860,1341,1367]" name="Spain" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Spain</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[914,1014,1341,1367]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[1024,1123,1341,1367]" name="Portugal" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: three provinces all over the country (this study), and Beira Alta (
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[561,814,1376,1403]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,1304,1547]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1413,1439]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded from an array of biotopes, including brackish marshes, mixed forest / orchard, and a river bank. Its ecology in the rest of Europe is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,1304,1547]" box="[199,456,1484,1511]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1484,1511]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
4.6 (rare).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,1304,1547]" box="[199,547,1520,1547]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1520,1547]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Activity period.</emphasis>
June–August.
</paragraph>
